cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and dependency parsing. The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the focus on improving parsing for agglutinative languages suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) due to the need for handling complex morphological structures.
